FBIS4-8059 "dreeu069_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported Serb Troops Crossing Drina River AU1004135394 Paris AFP in English 1345 GMT 10 Apr 94 AU1004135394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Zagreb, April 10 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb troops on Sunday began crossing the Drina river just south of the besieged Moslem town of Gorazde following a massive artillery offensive, the UN High Commissioner for Refugees announced. The soldiers began crossing the river shortly after 3:00 p.m. (1300 GMT), the UNHCR spokesman in Zagreb, Peter Kessler said. The river had marked the front line between the warring forces.
